OL,3,CCouncillors resign from Labour Party
OL,4,Ccondemning PM's leadership
OL,6,FLabour, however, maintains that the
OL,7,Fselection process followed the usual
OL,8,Fprocedures.
OL,10,FIn 2023, the constituency Labour
OL,11,FParty's executive committee resigned,
OL,12,Faccusing the national executive
OL,13,Fcommittee of blocking local councillor
OL,14,FGreg Marshall from standing in
OL,15,FBroxtowe.
OL,17,FLabour's Juliet Campbell ultimately
OL,18,Fwon the Broxtowe seat in the 2024
OL,19,Fgeneral election landslide.
